    {
      "类型": "method",
      "名称": "easing",
      "返回值": "SimpleAnimatorOptions",
      "所属模块": "未知模块",
      "功能描述": "Set time curve of the animation. For details about the supported types. linear The animation speed keeps unchanged. ease The animation starts and ends at a low speed, cubic-bezier(0.25, 0.1, 0.25, 1.0). ease-in The animation starts at a low speed, cubic-bezier(0.42, 0.0, 1.0, 1.0). ease-out The animation ends at a low speed, cubic-bezier(0.0, 0.0, 0.58, 1.0). ease-in-out The animation starts and ends at a low speed, cubic-bezier(0.42, 0.0, 0.58, 1.0). fast-out-slow-in Standard curve, cubic-bezier(0.4, 0.0, 0.2, 1.0). linear-out-slow-in Deceleration curve, cubic-bezier(0.0, 0.0, 0.2, 1.0). fast-out-linear-in Acceleration curve, cubic-bezier(0.4, 0.0, 1.0, 1.0). friction Damping curve, cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.0, 0.2, 1.0). extreme-deceleration Extreme deceleration curve, cubic-bezier(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0). sharp Sharp curve, cubic-bezier(0.33, 0.0, 0.67, 1.0). rhythm Rhythm curve, cubic-bezier(0.7, 0.0, 0.2, 1.0). smooth Smooth curve, cubic-bezier(0.4, 0.0, 0.4, 1.0). cubic-bezier(x1, y1, x2, y2) You can customize an animation speed curve in the cubic-bezier() function. The x and y values of each input parameter must be between 0 and 1. Step curve. The number must be set and only an integer is supported, step-position is optional. It can be set to start or end. The default value is end.",
      "注释信息": [
        "@param { string } curve - if not set, default is ease.",
        "@returns { SimpleAnimatorOptions }",
        "@syscap SystemCapability.ArkUI.ArkUI.Full",
        "@crossplatform",
        "@atomicservice",
        "@since arkts {'1.1':'18','1.2':'20'}",
        "@arkts 1.1&1.2"
      ],
